 savings bank swell by millions","body":"Before going west, Kilbourn rose from teller to treasurer of the Middletown Savings Bank across the 1870s, a period in which its deposits increased by several millions. He had begun his working life as purser aboard the steamship Liberty, running between New York and Havana."},{"number":4,"category":"character","header":"A churchman who built a mansion out West","body":"An elder and former treasurer of Pueblo’s First Presbyterian Church, Kilbourn built a prominent 1896 mansion where the family lived with domestic staff. His business reach extended to mining ventures across Nevada, California, and Colorado and a real-estate and loan agency."}],"career":[{"role":"Purser","organization":"Steamship Liberty (New York–Havana)","start_year":1864,"end_year":1865},{"role":"Clerk","organization":"Russell Manufacturing Co., Middletown","start_year":1865,"end_year":1870},{"role":"Teller, asst. secretary, treasurer","organization":"Middletown Savings Bank","start_year":1870,"end_year":1879},{"role":"Teller, assistant cashier","organization":"First National Bank, Pueblo","start_year":1881,"end_year":1884},{"role":"Receiver of Public Moneys","organization":"U.S. Land Office, Pueblo (appt. Pres. Cleveland)","start_year":1885,"end_year":1890},{"role":"Treasurer","organization":"Pueblo City Schools","start_year":1884,"end_year":null}],"education":[{"institution_name":"Daniel H. Chase’s Private School","relationship":"student","degree":"Preparatory"},{"institution_name":"Wesleyan University","relationship":"student","years":"to junior year","degree":"Left during junior year"}],"slug":"jonathan-burwell-kilbourn-1843"},"I01792":{"id":"I01792","classification":{"is_thomas_descendant":false,"is_talcott_descendant":false,"is_easter_egg":false,"generation_from_thomas":null},"bio":{"display_name":"Mary Adeline Douglas Kilbourn","first_name":"Mary Adeline","last_name":"Kilbourn","married_names":[],"maiden_name":"Douglas","photo_url":"https://res.cloudi